page.title: 01LANDSCAPE
page.content: Our area has a lot of uneven land the highest point is at the bottom edge which is 68 metres high.There is a lot more farmland than built up areas.There are a lot of nurserys doted around,its probably beacause of the amount of grass and farm land. There is a railway track running through the middle of Hockley. There is a station just outside of our area. There are a lot of wooded areas, the largest wood is the Great Bull Wood. Hockley is very high compared with Hullbridge. We have a rifle range and a country club called the Dome and one police station. There is one primary school and one secondary school in our area. Hockley and Hullbridge both have alot of houses and their own shopping areas although these are quite small.
